loom (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Major update with theme switching and enhanced plugin system
  * NEW: Multiple themes - Gruvbox, Dracula, and Catppuccin Mocha
  * NEW: Theme switching with Ctrl+Shift+T or Tools menu
  * NEW: Theme Switcher Plugin v1.2 with metadata support
  * NEW: Dynamic theme loading without restart
  * NEW: Config-based theme selection in config.lua
  * ENHANCED: Plugin system with proper validation and metadata
  * ENHANCED: Dynamic menu updates based on plugin status
  * ENHANCED: Tools menu integration for plugin actions
  * ENHANCED: Keybinding consistency for all plugin actions
  * ENHANCED: AutoFormat plugin with Ctrl+Shift+F and menu access
  * FIXED: Theme switcher boolean configuration being ignored
  * FIXED: Theme switching only working once (config update issue)
  * FIXED: Plugin keybindings showing errors when plugins disabled
  * FIXED: Menu items always visible regardless of plugin status
  * IMPROVED: Plugin loading sequence and menu refresh logic
  * IMPROVED: Plugin validation for enabled/auto_load settings

 -- dexter-xd <dexter-xd@users.noreply.github.com>  Mon, 01 Sep 2025 19:51:00 +0530

loom (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial beta release of Loom text editor
  * Fast, minimal, and customizable text editor built with C++ and Qt
  * Features Lua scripting for configuration and plugins
  * Includes syntax highlighting for multiple programming languages
  * Multi-tab interface with customizable keybindings
  * Gruvbox theme for comfortable coding
  * Plugin system with AutoSave and AutoFormat plugins
  * AutoFormat plugin supports clang-format, prettier, black, stylua, rustfmt
  * Line numbers with optional relative numbering
  * Find & Replace functionality
  * Cross-platform compatibility

 -- dexter-xd <dexter-xd@users.noreply.github.com>  Mon, 01 Sep 2025 